/31&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 142007P&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Yes&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped on crossing&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: no&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, cantilever fls, standard fls, highway traffic Signals, audible, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 4&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;VEHICLE WAS STOPPED IN THE RIGHT OF WAY, Q37508 PASSED THE VEHICLE WITHOUT STRIKING. Q35808 TRAVELING EASTBOUND STRUCK THE VEHICLE PUSHING IT INTO THE Q37508. OCCUPANT WAS OUT OF THE VEHICLE ATTEMPTING TO ALERT THE AUTHORITIES THAT HER VEHICLE WAS FOULING THE RIGHT OF WAY. PROTECTION ALSO AT CROSSING: PAVEMENT MARKINGS (RR XING SYMBOLS).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2011/07/09&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 142007P&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity T