            <description>Crossing: 923040X&lt;br&gt;Road Name: PRIVATE in CLEVELAND, OH, CUYAHOGA County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: CWRO&lt;br&gt;Division: nan, MP: nan-0.0&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 4/1/2003 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=nan,nan&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=nan,nan&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 0.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 0.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: nan&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 8&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;CREW WAS SHOVING 4 LOADS FROM HEIDTMAN TO SHIP.  CONDUCTORS SAW A SEMI APPROACHING THE RAIL CROSSING AND HAD A FEELING HE WASN'T GOING TO STOP.  HE TOLD THE ENGINEER TO DUMP IT AND BOTH CONDUCTORS DISMOUNTED THE CAR.  THE LEAD CAR IMPACTED THE TRAILER AND STOPPED ABOUT 5 FEET AFTER IMPACT.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2015/11/11&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923040X&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dawn&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 2&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;1557 WAS TRAVELING SOUTH ON 700 WITH TWO EMPTY GONS.  THE JONIK TRUCK WAS STOPPED AT GATE 5 AND BEGAN TO MOVE TOWARDS 700 TRACK INTO THE PATH OF THE LOCOMOTIVE. LIGHTS FLASHER AND BELLS WERE ALL ACTIVE ALONG WITH ENGINEER BLOWING AIR HORN.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2014/01/30&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923040X&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: south&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Drove around or thru the gate&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, audible&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Wet&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 3&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;CREW 231 HAD SIX EMPTY AND FOUR LOADED IRON LADLES.  AS THEY PULLED EAST ON TRACK 915, THE ENGINEER SAW A VAC-TRUCK CLOSE TO THE RAIL AT THE DIRT ROAD CROSSING.  HE MADE AN EMERGENCY BRAKE APPLICATION BUT WAS UNABLE TO STOP BEFORE STRIKING THE RIGHT FRONT FENDER AND MIRROR OF THE TRUCK.  CONDUCTOR WAS ON GROUND AT SWITCH AT WEST END OF DRAG.  TRUCK DRIVER AND PASSENGER EXITED TRUCK PRIOR TO COLLISION. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2010/10/27&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923040X&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped on crossing&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: no&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: &lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 4&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;SECURITY OFFICER WAS DRIVING UNIT 592 FROM THE UPPER DOCK OUT TO GATS 5 AND WAS HEADING BACK TO GATE 1 AS IT WAS THE END OF HER SHIFT. ENGINE 211 WAS PULLING A DRAG OF 9 BOTTLE CARS SOUTH ON TRACK 911 SOUTH SIDE OF C-5 BLAST FURNACE. AS THE VEHICLE CROSSED TRACK 911 IT WAS STRUCK BY THE LOCOMOTIVE ON THE PASSENGER SIDE DOOR. THE LOCOMOTIVE ENGINEER HAD LOOKED NORTH AND DID NOT SEE THE VEHICLE, HE THEN LOOKED BACK TO HIS CONDUCTOR AND WHEN HE LOOKED NORTH AGAIN, THE TRUCK WAS ON THE TRACK. THE LO&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2009/12/23&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923040X&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: pick-up truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Rail equipment&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Snow&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: permanent structure&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: &lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 5&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;THE DRIVER OF THE TRUCK WAS INFORMED BY THE COKE DUMP STATION OPERATOR TO DRIVE TO THE LOCATION OF THE INCIDENT AND TURN AROUND TO COME INTO THE STATION FROM THE OPPISITE DIRECTION. THE AREA THAT WAS USED TO TURN AROUND HAS THE TRACKS PAVED OVER AND IS ONE BIG ASPHALTED AREA WITH NO SIGNALS BUT DOES HAVE A COUPLE OF FLASHING LIGHTS AND SIGNS. THE CONDUCTOR WAS STANDING ON THE GROUND WAVING HIS ARMS IN THE AIR. THE TRUCK DRIVER SPED UP INSTEAD OF STOPPING AND THE TRAILER WAS STRUCK BY THE COKE HO&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2009/10/27&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923040X&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 6&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;CREW WAS PULLING 9 CARS OUT OF C-5 ON 914 TRACK WHEN THE CONDUCTOR SAW THE TRUCK PULL THROUGH THE SECURITY GATE AND HEAD TOWARD 911 TRACK HE ALERTED THE ENGINEER THAT THE TRUCK WAS IN THE AREA. THE TRUCK APPEARED TO STOP OR NEARLY STOP AT 914 TRACK CROSSING AND THEN CROSSED THE TRACK. BY THIS TIME THE CREW WAS SHOVING BACK INTO 914 TRACK WHEN THE 65 LADLE HIT THE TRUCK BEHIND THE PASSENGERS SIDE DOOR, NO ONE WAS HURT.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2007/09/07&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923040X&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 7&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;THE CREW WAS BRINGING IN 8 LOADS OF SCRAP TO WEIGH AT THE RAIL SCALE.  WHEN THEY APPROACHED 5 GATE A TRUCK LOAD OF COKE STARTED A CROSS THE X-ING AND THE ENGINEER STARTED TO BRAKE HIS TRAIN.  HE PUT THE TRAIN INTO EMERGENCY AND STRUCK THE TRUCK ON THE CROSSING.  NO ONE WAS HURT.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2004/01/16&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923040X&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: yard&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: standard fls&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 8&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;CREW WAS LEAVING THE SHOP WITH A LIGHT LOCOMOTIVE.  THE HEAD MAN SIGNALED THE TRUCK TO STOP WHICH HE DID.  THEN THE TRUCK DRIVER STARTED UP AND STRUCK THE LOCOMOTIVE ON THE LEFT FRONT CORNER BEHIND THE STEP WELL.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2003/12/09&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923040X&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Light loco/s (moving)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dawn&lt;br&gt;Weather: Rain&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Light loco(s)&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: siding&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;</description>
