br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 523793Y&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: other motor veh.&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dusk&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Drove around or thru the gate&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: injured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, standard fls, audible, cross bucks, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 4&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;Q26420 TRAVELING EAST ON #2 TRACK WAS STRUCK BY A STOLEN DODGE CARAVAN.  THIS HAPPENED WHILE POLICE WERE IN A HIGH SPEED PURSUIT. VAN HIT LINE 56 CNA 704698 (CAUSED DAMAGE TO AIR LINE ON SOUTH SIDE WEST END OF CAR). AFTER STRIKING TRAIN WITH THE DRIVER TRIED TO ESCAPE FROM THE POLICE BY CLIMBING UNDER THE MOVING TRAIN.  THIS RESULTED IN HIS ARM BEING CUT OFF. PROTECTION ALSO AT CROSSING: ADVANCE WARNING AND PAVEMENT MARKINGS (RR XING SYMBOLS). DRIVER WAS A JUVENILE.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2015/05/22&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 523793Y&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: van&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Wen thru the gate&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: injured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, standard fls, audible, cross bucks, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 5&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;Q00417 WAS STRUCK BY VEHICLE AT ROAD CROSSING ON ERIE STREET IN WILLOUGHBY OHIO. PROTECTION ALSO AT CROSSING: ADVANCE WARNING AND PAVEMENT MARKINGS (STOP LINES &amp; RR XING SYMBOLS).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2015/10/18&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 523793Y&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Rail equipment&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Drove around or thru the gate&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: injured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, standard fls, audible, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Wet&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 6&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;Q15602 STRUCK VEHICLE AT ERIE STREET CROSSING. PROTECTION ALSO AT CROSSING: ADVANCE WARNING AND PAVEMENT MARKINGS.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2014/01/02&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 523793Y&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Snow&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Drove around or thru the gate&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, standard fls, audible, cross bucks, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Snow/slush&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 7&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;Q81126 STRUCK A JEEP AT A CROSSING RESULTING IN A FATALITY.^                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2005/11/26&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 523793Y&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: other motor veh.&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Drove around or thru the gate&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: killed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, standard fls, audible&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 8&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;97 DODGE 4 DOOR MADE CONTACT WITH CSXT TRAIN Q10820 AT 1715 HOURS CAUSING SEVERE DAMAGE TO FRONT OFAUTOMOBILE. NO INJURIES REPORTED. STILL UNDER INVESTIGATION AT WILLOUGHBY POLICE.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2000/07/20&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 523793Y&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Rail equipment&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped on crossing&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, cantilever fls, audible, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;</description>
