            <name>923039D</name>
            <description>Crossing: 923039D&lt;br&gt;Road Name: PRIVATE in CLEVELAND, OH, CUYAHOGA County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: CWRO&lt;br&gt;Division: nan, MP: nan-0.0&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 4/1/2003 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=nan,nan&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=nan,nan&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 0.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 0.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: nan&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 8&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;221 CREW WAS SPOTTING LOADED CARS INTO MILL DOOR.  AS THE CREW WERE COMING AROUND THE CORNER OF THE MILL DOOR, THEY SAW A TRUCK BACKING UP OVER THE RAIL.  THE CONDUCTOR TOLD THE ENGINEER TO STOP, BUT THE LEAD CAR COLLIDED WITH THE REAR OF THE TRUCK BED. THERE APPEARED TO BE NO STRUCTURAL DAMAGE TO THE RAIL CAR OR TRUCK.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2018/09/27&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923039D&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: &lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 2&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;WHILE RE-SPOTTING 752 TRACK THE 321 JOB STRUCK A COMPANY OWNED CARRYALL TRUCK, CARRYING 3 COILS ON THE CROSSING PRIOR TO ENTERING THE BUILDING.  THE CONDUCTOR WAS RIDING THE SIDE OF NS 210489 AND SAW THAT A COIL TRACTOR WAS STOPPED AT THE CROSSING ON THE WEST SIDE (SAME SIDE AS HE WAS RIDING) OF THE TRACK.  HE THEN NOTICED A CARRYALL TRUCK ON THE OPPOSITE SIDE PULLING INTO THE TRAIN'S PATH.  HE TOLD THE ENGINEER TO STOP AND DISMOUNTED THE CAR BEFORE THE TRUCK COLLIDED WITH THE CAR.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2017/08/17&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923039D&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: south&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: opposite side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 3&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;COIL TRACTOR #15 WAS FOULING TRACK 751 CROSSING AND WAS STRUCK LIGHTLY BY THE FRONT OF THE 1557 WHICH WAS PULLING 7 LOADED HOT CARS FROM THE BUILDING.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2014/04/10&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923039D&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: other motor veh.&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 4&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;WHILE SHOVING CARS NORTH OUT OF TRACK 762, CONDUCTOR RIDING THE LEAD OF THE MOVEMENT, A LOADED TANK TRUCK OF HCL PULLED OUT IN FRONT OF THE MOVEMENT WITHOUT STOPPING FOR THE CROSSING.  CONDUCTOR SAW THE TRUCK MOVE OUT IN FRONT OF THEM AND TOLD THE ENGINEER TO PUT THE TRAIN IN EMERGENCY.  CONDUCTOR THEN BAILED OFF THE CARS.  THE NORTH END OF THE CUT OF CARS STRUCK THE TRAILER OF THE TRUCK CAUSING IT TO BE SHOVED ACROSS THE CROSSING AND TIPPING IT ON ITS SIDE, SPILLING HCL.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2013/11/15&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923039D&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Highway user&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: highway user&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 5&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;THE 21 JOB WAS ORDERED TO SWITCH 782 TRACK AND HAD COMPLETED THE SWITCH.  THE CONDUCTOR MADE HIS CUT AND TOLD ENGINEER TO GO AHEAD INTO THE ROADWAY.  A SILVER DODGE PICKUP TRUCK FAILED TO OBEY THE FLASHING LIGHTS AND BELLS THAT WERE ACTIVATED DURING THIS ENTIRE 782 SWITCH.  ENGINEER TRIED TO STOP THE LOCOMOTIVE BUT WAS UNABLE TO AND STRUCK THE LEFT REAR QUARTER PANEL.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2012/12/21&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923039D&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: pick-up truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Light loco/s (moving)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Snow&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Light loco(s)&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: audible&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Wet&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 6&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;CREW WAS SHOVING INTO 782 TRACK.  THE CONDUCTOR SAW A PICK-UP TRUCK CROSS THE TRACKS FROM THE EAST SIDE.  THE TRUCK MADE A U-TURN AND RE-CROSSED THE TRACKS FROM THE WEST SIDE.  THE CONDUCTOR WAVED HIS LANTERN AT THE DRIVER TO GET HIM TO STOP AND TOLD THE ENGINEER TO STOP BUT THE DRIVER CONTINUED ON BEING STUCK BY A SLAB STORAGE CAR CUVA 23990.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2006/06/23&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923039D&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: pick-up truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: yard&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: standard fls&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 7&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2006/08/16&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923039D&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Highway user&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: yard&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 8&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;TRAINMAN WAS RIDING THE LEADING END OF THE CARS WHEN A COIL LOADER STARTED TO CROSS IN FRONT OF HIM. THE TRAINMAN SHINED HIS LANTERN AT THE DRIVER BUT HE DIDN`T STOP AND WAS HIT BY THE RAIL CAR.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2002/10/24&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923039D&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: other motor veh.&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: yard&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: unknown&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;</description>
