        <Placemark id="58">
            <name>153762C</name>
            <description>Crossing: 153762C&lt;br&gt;Road Name: WEST TEMPLE STREET in WASHINGTON COURT HOUSE, OH, FAYETTE County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: IORY&lt;br&gt;Division: NORTHERN, MP: nan-233.18&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 6/19/2020 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=39.5359209,-83.444355&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=39.5359209,-83.444355&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 25.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 2.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: 1433.0&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: 2004.0&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 8&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;TRAIN CREW WAS SHOVING OVER THE CROSSING. CONDUCTOR WAS PROVIDING PROTECTION AT THE CROSSING. A 2006 CHEVY TRAILBLAZER TRAVELING THE WRONG WAY OFF OF A ONE WAY STREET ATTEMPTED TO CROSS IN FRONT OF THE TRAIN WHILE THE SHOVE MOVE WAS IN PROCESS AND WAS STRUCK BY THE REAR CAR OF THE TRAIN. NO PAVEMENT MARKINGS PRESENT NOR RAILROAD WARNING DEVICES FACED IN THE DIRECTION OF TRAVEL DUE TO NO MOTOR VEHICLES BEING DESIGNED TO TRAVEL IN THAT DIRECTION.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2023/04/13&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 153762C&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: other&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: yard&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: opposite side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: flagged by crew&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 2&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;CONDUCTOR FLAGGED CROSSING AND DIRECTED TRAIN ACROSS. MOTORIST DROVE UP AND ATTEMPTED TO BEAT THE TRAIN ACROSS THE HIGHWAY-RAILROAD GRADE CROSSING AND WAS STRUCK. DRIVER FLED SCENE IN VEHICLE. NO INFORMATION COULD BE RETRIEVED OTHER THAN IT BEING AN AUTOMOBILE, A FEMALE DRIVER, LIGHT VEHICLE DAMAGE, AND THE SEQUENCE OF EVENTS THAT TOOK PLACE.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2023/07/10&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 153762C&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: yard&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: flagged by crew&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 3&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;THE CONDUCTOR WAS FLAGGING THE CROSSING, BROUGHT THAT MOVEMENT TO A STOP, JUST BEFORE THE VEHICLE HIT THE LAST CAR OF THE TRAIN. PRIOR TO THIS, THE VEHILCE WAS STOPPED AT A STOP SIGN. PAVEMENT MARKINGS PRESENT.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2022/12/16&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 153762C&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (standing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, flagged by crew&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 4&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;TRAIN CREW WAS ACTIVELY SHOVING OVER A CROSSING PROTECTED BY THE CONDUCTOR ON THE GROUND WHEN A VEHICLE APPROACHED THE CROSSING AND STOPPED AT THE STOP SIGN. HIGHWAY MOTORIST ATTEMPTED TO DRIVE AROUND THE LEADING END OF THE MOVEMENT, BUT WAS UNABLE TO AND STRUCK THE SIDE OF THE RAILCAR. NO INJURIES TO THOSE INVOLVED.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2017/11/22&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 153762C&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Rail equipment&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks, flagged by crew&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 5&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;HIGHWAY MOTORIST ATTEMPTED TO TURN EAST BOUND ONTO WEST TEMPLE STREET AND IGNORED FLAGGER AND STRUCK THE LEADING RAILCAR.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2017/01/25&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 153762C&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Rain&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: permanent structure&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: standard fls, audible, stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Wet&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 6&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;WCH-C LOCAL CREW WAS SHOVING OVER WEST TEMPLE STREET AND VETERANS WAY IN WASHINGTON COURTHOUSE, OHIO, WHEN A VEHICLE HAD STOPPED IN THE FOUL OF THE CROSSING. THE CROSSING HAD LIGHTS AND GATES ON ALL FOUR CORNERS AND WAS FULLY FUNCTIONING AS INTENDED. THE CONDUCTOR WAS WALKING AHEAD OF THE MOVE AND NOTICED THE VEHICLE CAME UP BEHIND THEM DURING THE SHOVE MOVE. HE WARNED THE DRIVER TO GET OFF THE CROSSING, DRIVER ATTEMPTED TO PUT THE CAR IN REVERSE BUT WAS UNABLE TO VACATE THE CROSSING&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2017/07/16&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 153762C&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dusk&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped on crossing&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, audible, stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 7&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;ENGINEER WAS IN THE PROCESS OF MOVING LITE LOCOMOTIVE FROM THE WYE TRACK TO THE MAINT RACK WHEN A CAR PULLED OUT IN FRONT OF A LIGHT LOCOMOTIVE ON TEMPLE STREET.  CROSSING IS EQUIPPED WITH CROSSBUCKS FOR THE WYE TRACK AND FLASHERS FOR THE MAIN TRACK.  WITNESS STATES THAT THE ENGINEER WAS SOUNDING HORN.  DRIVER OF VEHICLE STATES HE HAD RADIO ON.  POLICE REPORT SHOWS FAILURE TO YIELD BY MOTORIST.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2008/06/04&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 153762C&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Light loco/s (moving)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dusk&lt;br&gt;Weather: Rain&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Light loco(s)&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 8&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;VEHICLE STOPPED TOO CLOSE TO TRACK; TRAIN SIDESWIPED PASSENGER SIDE.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2006/12/07&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 153762C&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: south&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped on crossing&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: standard fls&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;</description>
