            <name>923043T</name>
            <description>Crossing: 923043T&lt;br&gt;Road Name: PRIVATE in CLEVELAND, OH, CUYAHOGA County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: CWRO&lt;br&gt;Division: nan, MP: nan-0.0&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 4/1/2003 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=nan,nan&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=nan,nan&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 0.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 0.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: nan&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 6&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;THE 221 JOB JUST PICKED UP 14 EMPTY COKE HOPPERS FROM 963 AND WAS SHOVING DOWN 700 TRACK TO 720 TRACK. THE CONDUCTORS WERE RIDING THE SHOVE MOVE GIVING THE ENGINEER DISTANCE TO GO AND THEY WERE TRAVELING WEST TOWARDS THE TEEN YARD WHEN THEY NOTICED THAT THE TRUCK AT THE 719/702 CROSSING STOPPED, THE TRAIN WAS ABOUT 1 CAR LENGTH AWAY WHEN  THEY SEEN THE TRUCK DRIVER STARTED TO ROLL INTO THE CROSSING BOTH CONDUCTOR DISMOUNTED THE TRAIN AND TOLD THE ENGINEER THAT WILL DO JUST PRIOR TO THE COLLISION&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2022/10/03&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923043T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: yard&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: yes&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 2&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;THE 311 JOB WAS SHOVING 2 LOADS AND 1 EMPTY BOTTLE IN ON TRACK 99 WHEN THE PICKUP TRUCK STOP HIS VEHICLE IN THE ROAD CROSSING CAUSING THE 79 BOTTLE WHICH WAS THE LEAD END BOTTLE STRIKING THE LEFT SIDE FRONT FENDER AND GRILL ON THE PICKUP TRUCK.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2022/09/20&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923043T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: pick-up truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 3&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;THE 224 JOB WAS SHOVING 2 LOADED SCRAP CARS FROM THE SOUTH END OF SENECA YARD INTO THE INTAKE USING THE EAST BOUND TRACK, WHEN A TRUCK HAULING COKE FROM THE MIDDLE DOCK PROCEEDED TO MAKE A LEFT HAND TURN TOWARDS THE EASTBOUND TRACK IN FRONT OF THE SHOVE MOVE.  THE CONDUCTOR TOLD THE ENGINEER TO STEADY UP &amp; BLOW THE HORN, AT WHICH TIME THE ENGINEER DUMPED THE AIR AND MADE CONTACT WITH THE TRUCK.  THE CONDUCTOR JUMPED OFF THE GON AND WAS TAKEN TO THE CLINIC.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2021/09/23&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923043T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Highway user&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: yard&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 4&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;THE 121 JOB WAS PROCEEDING LIGHT ENGINE NORTH ON THE NSS MAIN WHILE A STEIN EUCLID (DUMP TRUCK) WAS TRAVELING WEST ON THE ACCESS ROAD FROM THE WEST SIDE DOCK MADE CONTACT.  THE CREW MEMBERS RIDING ON THE REAR PLATFORM OF THE 1557 NOTICED A STEIN EUCLID THAT WAS TRAVELING WEST PULL UP TO THE CROSSING AND STOPPED FOR A SECOND, BUT THEN PULLED OUT IN FRONT OF THEM WHEN THEY WERE 1 ENGINE LENGTH AWAY.  THE TRAIN MADE CONTACT WITH THE STEIN EUCLID STRIKING THE LEFT REAR TIRE.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2020/04/10&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923043T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: other motor veh.&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Light loco/s (moving)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Light loco(s)&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Sand, Mud, Dirt, Oil, Gravel&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 5&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;124 JOB WAS SHOVING 18 CARS THROUGH SENECA ON THE MAIN AND STOPPED TO LINE THE X-OVER SWITCHES, THEN PROCEED SOUTH TO TRACK 480 WHEN CONDUCTOR SAW A EUCLID TRUCK STOP WHICH ALLOWED HIM TO CONTINUE THE MOVEMENT.  AS THE 124 JOB APPROACHED THE ROAD CROSSING THE EUCLID DRIVER PROCEEDED TO MOVE INTO THE PATH OF THE TRAIN.  THE CONDUCTOR JUMPED OFF THE LEAD CAR.  THE ENGINEER PUT THE TRAIN INTO EMERGENCY AND TRIED TO GET COMMUNICATION FROM HIS GROUNDMAN.  THE LEAD END CAR SHOVED THE EUCLID 55 FEET FR&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2016/04/27&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923043T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: south&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 6&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;AFTER SPOTTING W SIDE SLAB YARD, CREW PROCEEDED TO SHOVE EAST ON THE WESTBOUND MAIN TOWARDS SENECA YARD.  THERE WAS A TRUCK STOPPED ON THE ROAD NEAR THE MIDDLE DOCK AREA FACING THE ONCOMING TRAIN.  THE CREW PROCEEDED WITH THEIR MOVEMENT WHEN THE TRUCK PULLED OUT IN FRONT OF THEM.  THE CONDUCTOR BAILED OFF THE LEAD CAR BEFORE IT STRUCK THE TRUCK AND PUSHED IT 60 FT.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2012/11/21&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 923043T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Yard / switching&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: stop signs, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;</description>
