            <description>Crossing: 867103W&lt;br&gt;Road Name: STICKNEY AVENUE in TOLEDO, OH, LUCAS County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: CSX&lt;br&gt;Division: GREAT LAKES, MP: CTT-2.42&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 2/2/2021 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=41.708086,-83.5276194&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=41.708086,-83.5276194&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 10.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 1.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: 2468.0&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: 2008.0&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 3&lt;br&gt;Injured: 2&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;Y32122 WAS MOVING LITE ENGINE OVER CROSSING. THE LIGHTS FOR THE CROSSING WERE FLASHING. AS THEY APPROACHED THE CROSSING A SOUTHBOUND VEHICLE CROSSED OVER AND WAS STRUCK BY ENGINE CSXT 2517 ON THE PASSENGER SIDE AND WAS DRUG ABOUT 50 FEET WHEN THE LOCOMOTIVE CAME TO A STOP AND THE VEHICLE CONTINUED SOUTHBOUND ON STICKNEY AVENUE. THE POLICE WERE NOTIFIED AND WERE UNABLE TO LOCATE THE VEHICLE. AGE AND GENDER OF DRIVER UNKNOWN. PROTECTION ALSO AT CROSSING: ADVANCE WARNING.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2011/12/23&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 867103W&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: south&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Light loco/s (moving)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Light loco(s)&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: siding&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Stru