            <description>Crossing: 509368N&lt;br&gt;Road Name: E BROADWAY ST in PERRYSBURG, OH, WOOD County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: CSX&lt;br&gt;Division: GREAT LAKES, MP: QTE-7.56&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 4/8/2021 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=41.5436828,-83.511398&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=41.5436828,-83.511398&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 10.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 0.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: 55.0&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: 792.0&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: 2007.0&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: 55.0&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 5&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;DRIVER FAILED TO YIELD AT RAILROAD CROSSING AND STRUCK THE SIDE OF THE TRAIN. RAILCARS ZVBX 76096 &amp; FPTX 84069 WERE SLIGHTLY DAMAGED BUT NOTHING DERAILED. NO INJURIES REPORTED. PROTECTION ALSO AT CROSSING: ADVANCE WARNING AND PAVEMENT MARKINGS (STOP LINES &amp; RR XING SYMBOLS).///                                                                                                                                                                                                                              &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2007/04/14&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 509368N&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Snow&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: cross bucks, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 2&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;Q39729 WAS TRAVELING OVER CROSSING WHEN VEHICLE RAN INTO THE 6TH RAILCAR (PLMX 135439). DRIVER NOT INJURED/PASSENGER INJURED. IN ADDITION TO CROSSING PROTECTION, CONDUCTOR WAS FLAGGING THE CROSSING. ALSO AT CROSSING: ADVANCE WARNING AND PAVEMENT MARKINGS. DRIVER CITED (TO DO WITH SPEED).                                                                                                                                                                                                                    &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2007/06/29&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 509368N&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: south&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Rail equipment&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle