            <description>Crossing: 473552V&lt;br&gt;Road Name: SEVILLE RD in LODI, OH, MEDINA County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: WE&lt;br&gt;Division: #N\A, MP: B-103.08&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 10/11/2021 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=41.0125236,-81.988574&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=41.0125236,-81.988574&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 40.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 8.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: 25.0&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: 756.0&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: 2007.0&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: 25.0&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Injured: 3&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 2&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;389-23 WAS TRAVELING WESTBOUND OVER MPB103.1, SEVILLE ROAD, WITH HEADLIGHT ON BRIGHT RINGING BELL AND SOUNDING HORN WHEN A SEMI TRUCK FAILED TO YIELD AT THE CROSSING AND WAS STRUCK BY THE TRAIN.  PERSON IN SEMI TRUCK WAS LIFE FLIGHTED TO HOSPITAL DUE TO HEAD TRAUMA.   

THE SPEED OF THE SEMI AND THE VEHICLE PROPERTY DAMAGE IS UNAVAILABLE TO US, NOTHING IN THE POLICE REPORT. 



&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2007/05/23&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 473552V&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: injured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: yes&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 2&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;228-06 WAS EASTBOUND APPROACHING MPB 103.1, SEVILLE ROAD, WITH HEADLIGHT AND DITCH LIGHTS BURNING, BELL AND WHISTLE SOUNDING, WHEN THEY STRUCK A TRACTOR TRAILER THAT FAILED TO YIELD AT THE CROSSING. THE TRACTOR TRAILER WAS SHOVED APPROXIMATELY 600 FEET.  UPON IMPACT THE DRIVERS SIDE FUEL TANK BECAME LODGED UNDER THE SNOW PLOW OF THE ENGINE EMLX 8529 CAUSING THE FUEL TANK TO RUPTURE AND CATCH FIRE. 

 
VEHICLE SPEED IS UNAVAILABLE TO US, NOTHING IN THE POLICE REPORT.
DAMAGE TO THE TRACTOR TRA&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2007/07/06&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 473552V&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck-trailer&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: east&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Rail equipment&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: injured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: yes&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 3&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;227-28 WAS WESTBOUND APPROACHING SEVILLE ROAD WITH HEADLIGHT ON BRIGHT RING BELL AND SOUNDING HORN WHEN A DUMP TRUCK FAILED TO YIELD AT THE CROSSING AND WAS STRUCK BY THE LEAD UNIT WE 4025, THE IMPACT RESULTED IN THE FUEL TANK ON THE WE 4025 BEING RIPPED OPEN AND LOSING APPROXIMATELY 2700 GALS OF FUEL.      NOTE: AT THE TIME OF THIS REPORT THE DRIVERS AGE AND ESTIMATED SPEED OF THE VEHICLE ARE UNAVALIBLE.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2006/04/28&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 473552V&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: truck&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units