            <description>Crossing: 152395T&lt;br&gt;Road Name: HANOVER STREET in HAMILTON, OH, BUTLER County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: CSX&lt;br&gt;Division: LOUISVILLE, MP: BE-25.06&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 1/12/2023 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=39.389972,-84.5574105&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=39.389972,-84.5574105&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 35.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 14.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: 1620.0&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: 1992.0&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 3&lt;br&gt;Killed: 1&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;A VEHICLE STRUCK THE SIDE OF LOCOMOTIVE CSXT 3353 FROM CSX TRAIN Q35110 AT THE HANOVER STREET CROSSING IN HAMILTON, OHIO.  MOTORIST FLED THE SCENE AFTER STRIKING THE TRAIN. AGE UNKNOWN.  PROTECTION ALSO AT CROSSING: PAVEMENT MARKINGS (STOP LINES &amp; RR XING SYMBOLS).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2020/05/10&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 152395T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dark&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Wen thru the gate&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, standard fls, audible, cross bucks, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 2&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;TRAIN Q134-29 STRUCK AND FATALLY WOUNDED PEDESTRIAN TRESPASSER AT CROSSING.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2017/07/26&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 152395T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: pedestrian&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dusk&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Other&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: killed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: no&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates, standard fls, audible&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 3&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;HWY-USER'S INFORMATION UNKNOWN.  TRAIN 174L004, ON DUTY IN CINCINNATI AT 17:00, WAS TRAVELING WEST ON THE CSX LINE WHEN IT STRUCK A DISABLE CAR ON THE ACTIVATED CROSSING AT HANOVER STREET, HAMILTON, OH.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2013/02/05&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 152395T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: west&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: dusk&lt;br&gt;Weather: Cloudy&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Yes&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped on crossing&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: no&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: gates&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: unknown&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 4&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;CROSSING WAS CLOSED TO HIGHWAY USERS DUE TO REPAIRS. MOTORIST DROVE AROUND A BARRICADE AND ROAD CLOSED SIGN THAT WAS PROTECTING THE CLOSED CROSSING AND WAS STRUCK BY Q22602. ALSO AT CROSSING: ADVANCED WARNING &amp; PAVEMENT MARKINGS (STOP LINES &amp; RRX SYMBOLS). AGE &amp; GENDER OF DRIVER UNKNOWN.///                                                                                                                                                                                                                 &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2006/07/03&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 152395T&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: south&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pulling)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struc