            <name>525239P</name>
            <description>Crossing: 525239P&lt;br&gt;Road Name: READING ROAD/TYLERSVILLE ROAD in MASON, OH, WARREN County&lt;br&gt;Crossing Closed?: No&lt;br&gt;Railroad: IORY&lt;br&gt;Division: NORTHERN, MP: nan-10.52&lt;br&gt;Last Update: 6/19/2020 0:00&lt;br&gt;Google Maps: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;q=39.351859,-84.321484&lt;br&gt;Street View: https://maps.google.com/?t=k&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=39.351859,-84.321484&lt;br&gt;Railroad Speed: 10.0&lt;br&gt;Railroad Traffic: 0.0&lt;br&gt;Road LRSID: nan&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;Road AADT: 5171.0&lt;br&gt;AADT Year: 2003.0&lt;br&gt;Road Speed: nan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Number of Fatalities/Injuries:&lt;br&gt;Uninjured: 4&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 1&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;TRAIN APPROACHED HIGHWAY GRADE CROSSING. ROADWAY TRAFFIC STOPPED IN COMPLIANCE WITH TRAFFIC LIGHTS BEING RED. TRAIN BEGAN SHOVING TOWARDS AND OVER THE CROSSING. A SUV CROSSOVER WAS IN THE RIGHT TURN LANE (WITH TRAIN TO THEIR RIGHT), STOPPED. REPORTEDLY, HIS TRAFFIC SIGNAL TURNED TO A GREEN RIGHT ARROW AND HE DROVE WHILE THE TRAIN WAS SHOVING OVER THE CROSSING. THE MOTOR VEHICLE REALIZED THE TRAIN WAS MOVING TOWARDS HIM AND WAS STRUCK. PAVEMENT MARKINGS PRESENT.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2020/03/03&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 525239P&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: other motor veh.&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Rain&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Yes&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Stopped and then proceeded&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: other&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: standard fls, highway traffic Signals, cross bucks, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Wet&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 2&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;WHILE SHOVING 5 EMPTIES WITH ONE LOCOMOTIVE NORTH ON THE MASON SUB, A VEHICLE STRUCK THE REAR RAIL CAR DUE TO FAILING TO COMPLY WITH A TRAFFIC DEVICE AT TYLERSVILLE ROAD&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2017/10/03&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 525239P&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Recorder&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: side of vehicle approach&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Yes&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: highway traffic Signals, cross bucks, other (specify)&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: female&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 3&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;WHILE R2-15 OCCUPIED TYLERSVILLE RD AND READING RD CROSSING, A CAR TRAVELING NORTH DROVE AROUND CARS IN THE RIGHT HAND TURN ONLY LANE, FAILED TO YIELD FOR FLASHING LIGHTS AND MADE AN ILLEGAL RIGHT HAND TURN STRIKING THE LEAD CAR DRAWBAR. NO INJURIES.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2014/03/15&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 525239P&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: auto&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: south&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Train (units pushing)&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck by highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Freight train&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: main&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: Yes&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: Yes&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: highway traffic Signals, cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: unknown&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Dry&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Incident 4&lt;br&gt;Incident Description: &lt;br&gt;A LOAD OF LUMBER, IC 624278, TRAVELING NORTH AND UNATTENDED ON THE MASON INDUSTRIAL TRACK AT MP 10.3 TYLERSVILLE ROAD STRUCK A MINIVAN CONTAINING FIVE OCCUPANTS - TWO ADULTS AND THREE CHILDREN.  THE RAILROAD CAR CONTINUED NORTH AFTER THE IMPACT WITH THE MINIVAN.  SPEED OF RAILCAR IS UNKNOWN.  INCIDENT UNDER INVESTIGATION.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Date (Y/M/D):&lt;br&gt;2005/06/14&lt;br&gt;State: Ohio&lt;br&gt;Xing Name: 525239P&lt;br&gt;The following values were translated from their original records;&lt;br&gt;Vehicle Type: van&lt;br&gt;Train Direction: north&lt;br&gt;Railroad Equipment: Cars moving&lt;br&gt;Accident Circumstances: Rail equipment struck highway user&lt;br&gt;Entity Transporting Hazard: Neither&lt;br&gt;Visibility: day&lt;br&gt;Weather: Clear&lt;br&gt;Type of Consist: Single car&lt;br&gt;Type of Track: industry&lt;br&gt;Train Speed Type: Estimated&lt;br&gt;Location of Warning: both sides&lt;br&gt;Crossing Warnings Connected with Highway: No&lt;br&gt;Lights at Crossing: Unknown&lt;br&gt;Motorist Passed Standing Hwy Vehicle: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Struck by Second Train: No&lt;br&gt;Motorist Action: Did not stop&lt;br&gt;Primary Obstruction of Track View: not obstructed&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver Casualty: uninjured&lt;br&gt;Highway Driver in Vehicle: yes&lt;br&gt;Report Filed: no&lt;br&gt;Type of Warning Device: cross bucks&lt;br&gt;Hazmat Released by: neither&lt;br&gt;Whistle Ban in Effect: no&lt;br&gt;Gender of Driver: male&lt;br&gt;Road Conditions: Unknown&lt;br&gt;</description>
